==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Ecstatic
<hw>Ec*stat"ic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <?/, fr. <?/:
cf. F. <ets>extatique</ets>. See <er>Ecstasy</er>, <pos>n.</pos>]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>Pertaining to, or caused by, ecstasy or excessive
emotion; of the nature, or in a state, of ecstasy; <as>as,
<ex>ecstatic</ex> gaze; <ex>ecstatic</ex> trance.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>This <qex>ecstatic</qex> fit of love and jealousy.</q>
<rj><qau>Hammond.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Delightful beyond measure; rapturous; ravishing;
<as>as, <ex>ecstatic</ex> bliss or joy</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Ecstatic</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Ecstatic
<hw>Ec*stat"ic</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>An enthusiast.</def>
<mark>[R.]</mark> <rj><au>Gauden.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Ecstatical</ent>⟦br⟧
